## Managing input files
Select one or more input files to view the available actions.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

The available actions depend on the file type.

Actions that are available on individual files may not be available on a multiple selection (for example, the **Inspect **action).

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Process**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-inputs#processing-an-input-file)

Start a new job for the selected input file.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Cancel**

Cancel the execution of the corresponding job.

> Warning

Canceled inputs cannot be recovered, but can be processed again.

> Note

This action is only available for input files in **Paused**, **Ignored **or **Susp ended **status.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Download**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-inputs#downloading-an-input-file)

Download the input file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Inspect**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-inputs#inspecting-an-input-file)

Open the **Inspect **panel to view more information on the input file.

> Tip

You may also hover on the name of an input file, click on the **... **icon that appears, and select one of the available actions from the context menu. For example:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

### Processing an input file
- Select an input file.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) ( **Process **) to start a new job for the selected input file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the release to process.

- Click **Process **to confirm.

### Downloading an input file
- Select an input file.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,)  (**Download**) to save a copy of the input file to your local filesystem.

> Note

Input files are downloaded in ZIP format.

> **Data retention period**

If the job is older than the configured data retention period of the tenant, the input data will automatically be removed from the system. The information of the input will still be visible in the Batch Jobs portal, but the **Download **button will be disabled and a warning shown.

### Inspecting an input file
The **Inspect **panel provides more information on the status and properties of the selected input file and of the corresponding job.

- Select an input file.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Inspect**), or click on the name of the file.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs - Inspect Panel](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-inspect-panel), section "Inspecting an input file".
